reviews.review_text:
Ta Da! And Yet Another Superb audience recording by Rango Keshavan, whom, I'm convinced, was the master of the Sony D-5 cassette deck and ECM-220 mikes. This recording really captures the moment in the entire frequency spectrum.

The band's performance that day was exemplary of the overall level of commitment the band had towards preserving their approach to providing good ol' party music. Nothing serious here, none the less, it's palpable.
Great Recording, Rango! Great show, and great recording.  Thanks, Rango!
Back in those days you could get Bird Song and Let it Grow in the same set. No rationing the first set jam songs to one per night.
